---
description: Every mutation / async action must show loading feedback to the user
alwaysApply: true
---

# Mutation Loading Feedback

**Every `useMutation` must give visible feedback while pending.** The user must always know something is happening. No silent async actions.

## Required for every mutation trigger

1. **Disable** the triggering element (`disabled={mutation.isPending}`)
2. **Show a spinner or loading state** (Mantine `loading` prop, `<Loader />`, or text change like "Deleting...")
3. **Prevent double-submission** (disabled handles this)

## Patterns

### Button with `loading` prop (preferred for Mantine buttons)

```tsx
<Button loading={mutation.isPending} onClick={handleSubmit}>
  Save
</Button>
```

### ActionIcon with spinner swap

```tsx
<ActionIcon disabled={isDeleting} onClick={() => onDelete(id)}>
  {isDeleting ? <Loader size={14} /> : <IconTrash size={16} />}
</ActionIcon>
```

### Custom button with text change

```tsx
<button onClick={handleExecute} disabled={mutation.isPending}>
  {mutation.isPending ? <Loader size={16} /> : <IconPlay size={16} />}
  <span>{mutation.isPending ? 'Searching...' : 'Execute'}</span>
</button>
```

## Per-item mutations in lists

When a list has one mutation shared across items (e.g. delete), track which item is pending:

```tsx
const deletingId = deleteMutation.isPending
  ? (deleteMutation.variables?.path?.id ?? null)
  : null

// Pass to each item
<Card isDeleting={deletingId === item.id} />
```

## Duplicate triggers

If the same action has multiple triggers (e.g. a header button and an empty-state button), **all** triggers must show loading state — not just one.
